parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: My name’s Fred, I live in London and I’m 17 years old.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: My mother is called Julia and my father is called Mark,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and I have one little brother who’s 11 years old who’s called Max.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I wake up at 7 and I usually get out of bed about 7.30

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: then I come downstairs and have breakfast.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Usually I have cereal for breakfast with orange juice,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: but sometimes I have toast with usually jam or honey.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: In my bag I have all my books for my lessons, like text books and books to write with,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I study drama, so if I have a play that I’m in then I have a script as well.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: And sometimes if I have orchestra or a music lesson I’ll take my cello,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: which is very heavy, so that’s not fun to take to school.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: And then I walk to school. I walk, because my school’s only...

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: it’s only in the centre of the town where I live so it’s only 15 minutes’ walk in the morning,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: which is good because it means I can sleep later.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: but if I meet someone on the way that goes to my school as well I’ll walk with them usually,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: because everyone is very friendly around here, it is a very nice area.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: The school is quite old, it’s been a school for about 400 years

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and it’s got about a 1000 students there in seven age groups and it’s only boys there.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Most people in England at my age don’t usually have to wear a uniform

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: but our schools... they sort of encourage it at our age.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Basically we have to wear a suit, just a black suit or dark suit, with a tie from the school.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: School starts at 8.30 and then we have two lessons which go until 10.15.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: And then 10.15 we have to go and register and have like a time just in a class with our teachers,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: not doing a lesson, just talking or whatever.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Some people play football, not many in my year,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: usually you can get something to eat or just sort of hang around and talk to your friends.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Then 11 till 12.40 we have two more lessons, and then lunchtime.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I can go into town to get my lunch, but most people have to stay in the school

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and eat the school food and British school food isn’t very nice.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Then we have two more lessons after lunch and we finish school at 3.30.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Usually I come home and I just sort of relax for a bit,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and that’s usually for maybe an hour. I read or I watch television.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: My mum gets home about... usually between 5.30 and 6

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and so we’ll usually eat dinner about 6.30.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I’ve played cello for maybe eight years now

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: and my mum can play the piano quite well,

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: so usually if I have a piece I’m learning for an exam, she’ll try and play along.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I live with my two parents.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: Then I pack my bag for school.

parameter.name: Text
parameter.value: I have pens and pencils usually.
